ce:section.ce:para:
As conditions were established to achieve better signal variation of photoluminescence from the GQDs-GSH-Fe3+ in the presence of neomycin (Table 4
                        ), signal response curves were constructed for other aminoglycosides (as sulfate): neomycin (with 5 primary amino groups), gentamicin (with 4 primary amino groups and 1 secondary amino group) and kanamycin (with 4 primary amino groups). In all cases, photoluminescence increased as quantities of aminoglycosides gradually increased in the nanoparticle dispersion (Fig. 7
                        ). The signal recoveries presented a linear trend (R2 above 0.99) when net photoluminescence (Ln–L0/L0) is normalized to the photoluminescence obtained before the addition of aminoglycosides. The sensitivities of the photoluminescence restoration curves induced by neomycin sulfate, kanamycin sulfate and gentamycin sulfate were respectively 0.054, 0.093 and 0.098 L mol−1 respectively.
